cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep learning network for pavement crack detection, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and feature extraction. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the design of the network architecture and the optimization of the features, which are related to machine learning (ML) techniques such as neural networks and optimization algorithms. Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper deals with pavement maintenance, which involves robotics (RO) and control (CR) techniques for automated inspection and repair. Therefore, cs.RO and cs.CR are also possible sub-categories.
